        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 11:35AM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 1135 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Twin Lakes, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Twin Lakes, Conway Summit, Devils Gate Summit, Robinson
Creek Campground, Bridgeport Reservoir, Junction U.S 395 And CA 108
(Sonora Junction), Buckeye Campground, Trumbull Lake Campground,
Bridgeport-Bryant Field Airport, Lundy Canyon Campground, and
Junction U.S 395 And CA 270 (Bodie Rd).
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
